12:20.125 --> 12:21.291
They’re here.

12:21.291 --> 12:23.750
Don’t sniff their fake flowers.

12:23.750 --> 12:25.208
(knocking)

12:25.208 --> 12:27.208
-Hey, Darryl.
-That floodlight you got on

12:27.208 --> 12:29.000
is flooding us out
of our own bedroom.

12:29.000 --> 12:31.291
We’re trying to get busy,
and you lit us up.

12:31.291 --> 12:33.333
-We’re already lit.
-Yeah, I’m sorry, Darryl.

12:33.333 --> 12:35.750
My wife made me install
this motion detector

12:35.750 --> 12:37.458
because there’s been
some crimes--

12:37.458 --> 12:38.625
-You know what a crime is?
-Mm.

12:38.625 --> 12:40.667
A crime is you interrupting
my sex life.

12:40.667 --> 12:42.709
Whoo-whoo-whoo-whoo-whoo, okay?

12:42.709 --> 12:44.500
Yeah, well,
I’ll unscrew the bulb.

12:44.500 --> 12:45.875
We like to get busy
in the dark,

12:45.875 --> 12:47.166
so I can pretend
I have both my feet again.

12:47.166 --> 12:48.166
You understand?

12:48.166 --> 12:49.875
I said I’ll
unscrew the bulb.

12:49.875 --> 12:51.166
Please unscrew the bulb.

12:51.166 --> 12:52.250
It’s hard to get back
into character

12:52.250 --> 12:53.291
when you’re role-playing, okay?

12:53.291 --> 12:54.458
-Okay?
-Yeah, mhm.

12:54.458 --> 12:55.375
Whew.

12:55.375 --> 12:57.875
♪

12:57.875 --> 13:00.875
JOAN: I wonder what the light
is missing now that it’s off.

13:00.875 --> 13:03.291
It’s things that you
don’t see that get you.

13:03.291 --> 13:06.250
Like brain-sucking amoeba
in the tap water.

13:08.083 --> 13:10.333
You don’t need any light
when you got me,

13:10.333 --> 13:11.792
or this Taser.

13:11.792 --> 13:13.417
That’s a TV remote.

13:13.417 --> 13:15.208
Yeah, but the bad guys
don’t know that,

13:15.208 --> 13:17.041
especially with the light off.

13:17.041 --> 13:19.834
John, please go outside and
make sure everything’s okay.

13:19.834 --> 13:21.625
You want me to check
when the light goes on,

13:21.625 --> 13:23.792
now you want me to check
when it doesn’t.

13:23.792 --> 13:26.083
And all the other times, too.

13:26.083 --> 13:27.458
♪

13:30.000 --> 13:31.083
What are you doing?

13:31.083 --> 13:32.792
Get back, or I’ll
kick you in the face!

13:32.792 --> 13:34.166
You get back!

13:34.166 --> 13:35.458
Is that a TV remote?

13:35.458 --> 13:37.125
You’re holding a fake leg.

13:37.125 --> 13:39.000
Oh, sorry, I thought
you were a clown.

13:39.000 --> 13:40.583
Were you stealing my trash?

13:40.583 --> 13:41.875
No, I...

13:41.875 --> 13:43.083
Okay, look.

13:43.083 --> 13:44.792
It’s been me
setting your light off.

13:44.792 --> 13:47.000
I’ve been hiding my fast-food
wrappers in your garbage can.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.000
Well, that’s weird.

13:48.000 --> 13:49.917
Why don’t you just hide
some vodka bottles

13:49.917 --> 13:52.542
or a dead body in there,
like normal people?

13:52.542 --> 13:54.542
Pam does not like me
to eat that kind of food.

13:54.542 --> 13:55.709
She’s freaking out
that I’m gonna

13:55.709 --> 13:58.000
endanger the livelihood
of my other leg.

13:58.000 --> 13:59.333
When she said "livelihood,"
I didn’t know

13:59.333 --> 14:00.375
what the hell
she was talking about--

14:00.375 --> 14:02.709
like this leg is earning money
for us or something.

14:02.709 --> 14:03.917
You know, Joan doesn’t like

14:03.917 --> 14:05.875
me eating fast food either.

14:05.875 --> 14:07.083
I thought you were Joan.

14:07.083 --> 14:08.333
I’m John.

14:08.333 --> 14:10.041
That’s what I said, Joan.

14:10.041 --> 14:13.625
♪

14:17.166 --> 14:18.417
Did you hear that?

14:18.417 --> 14:20.417
What? I didn’t hear anything.

14:20.417 --> 14:23.417
I did, I better go check it out.

14:25.750 --> 14:27.834
-Mmm.
-Oh, this is the life.

14:27.834 --> 14:29.625
Is it the life or not?

14:29.625 --> 14:31.792
-Ooh!
-Maybe tomorrow night,

14:31.792 --> 14:34.041
you could bring
a couple of good cigars.

14:34.041 --> 14:35.125
Oh.

14:35.125 --> 14:37.750
See, I’m not allowed
to do that either.

14:37.750 --> 14:38.667
I would love that.

14:38.667 --> 14:40.583
I would love a good stogie.

14:40.583 --> 14:43.583
-Oh, oh, cheers.
-Cheers, mm.

14:43.583 --> 14:44.709
Oh, I got a brain freeze.

14:44.709 --> 14:46.208
(groans)

14:46.208 --> 14:47.542
♪

14:47.542 --> 14:49.291
What are you doing up?
You can’t sleep either?

14:49.291 --> 14:51.458
I am not a great sleeper.

14:51.458 --> 14:53.166
I’ve actually woken up
in the middle

14:53.166 --> 14:55.417
of four different surgeries.

14:57.959 --> 15:00.875
♪

15:00.875 --> 15:02.750
-Mmm, oh, man.
-Oh, God.

15:02.750 --> 15:03.750
This is so good.

15:03.750 --> 15:05.041
Baby, you want in on that?

15:05.041 --> 15:06.834
-Yes, I do.
-Oh, come on.

15:06.834 --> 15:08.083
But now that we’re
not eloping,

15:08.083 --> 15:09.834
I’m on this crazy
juice diet for the wedding.

15:09.834 --> 15:10.917
(groans)

15:10.917 --> 15:13.208
Oh, I have to go to
the calligrapher’s

15:13.208 --> 15:14.834
for the invitations.

15:14.834 --> 15:17.917
-She gets to be fat.
-Mm.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.458
-Bye.
-Good-bye.

15:19.458 --> 15:21.125
Oh, hey!

15:21.125 --> 15:23.333
Listen, don’t do anything
in the common areas

15:23.333 --> 15:26.041
you don’t want me joining in on.

15:26.041 --> 15:27.166
-I been working out.
-Mm.

15:27.166 --> 15:29.125
I can lift both of you.

15:29.125 --> 15:30.375
Morning, Dougie.

15:30.375 --> 15:33.500
DOUGIE: Whoa, whoa, whoa!

15:33.500 --> 15:35.166
Who ate my pot roast?

15:35.166 --> 15:38.458
It wasn’t me, I have not
eaten anything in two weeks.

15:38.458 --> 15:40.166
Neither one of us ate
your pot roast, Dougie,

15:40.166 --> 15:42.583
just like neither one of us
ate your shark jerky.

15:42.583 --> 15:45.125
That sounds like the kind
of brave a man gets

15:45.125 --> 15:48.375
when he has a stomach
full of red meat.

15:48.375 --> 15:49.792
(huffs)

15:49.792 --> 15:52.542
I’m gonna turn around,
I’m gonna count to ten.

15:52.542 --> 15:54.125
I want whoever ate
that pot roast

15:54.125 --> 15:57.417
to put it back,
no questions asked.

15:57.417 --> 15:58.333
-Put it back?
-I don’t know.

15:58.333 --> 15:59.834
DOUGIE: One...

15:59.834 --> 16:01.959
COLLEEN: Okay, this one...

16:01.959 --> 16:04.375
Which font do you like best
for wedding invitations,

16:04.375 --> 16:07.458
Old English or Prison Tattoo?

16:07.458 --> 16:08.542
They’re the same.

16:08.542 --> 16:10.500
Well, then it shouldn’t be hard
for you to make a decision.

16:10.500 --> 16:11.750
(doorbell rings)

16:11.750 --> 16:13.500
All this wedding planning
is so hard

16:13.500 --> 16:16.250
for me to do on my own.

16:16.250 --> 16:18.792
MATT: Oh.

16:18.792 --> 16:21.417
Are you Colleen Ortega?

16:21.417 --> 16:22.417
Sure.

16:22.417 --> 16:23.792
Uh, Colleen,

16:23.792 --> 16:26.458
did you order something
from ChocolateFountains.com?

16:26.458 --> 16:28.709
Mm, no.

16:28.709 --> 16:29.875
What do you think it is?

16:32.500 --> 16:34.709
-Dougie, open up.
-I know you’re in there.

16:34.709 --> 16:36.792
The door’s warm.

16:36.792 --> 16:37.917
Ah.

16:37.917 --> 16:41.000
Did you go on my account
and order a chocolate fountain?

16:41.000 --> 16:43.166
Why would I need another one

16:43.166 --> 16:47.542
when this one serves
all of my chocolate needs?

16:47.542 --> 16:49.834
(sucks teeth)

16:49.834 --> 16:51.458
COLLEEN:
Oh, wow, Celeste,

16:51.458 --> 16:53.542
that really clears it
all up.

16:53.542 --> 16:55.250
Thank you.

16:55.250 --> 16:56.458
So you really bought it, huh?

16:56.458 --> 16:59.333
Yeah, and apparently
I spent three hours

16:59.333 --> 17:00.917
on the phone last night
with customer service

17:00.917 --> 17:03.000
discussing wedding fountains
and you,

17:03.000 --> 17:06.166
and our first sexual experience.

17:06.166 --> 17:07.625
-What?
-Don’t worry.

17:07.625 --> 17:10.500
She said that you sound like
a very generous lover.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.000
And you don’t remember
any of this?

17:12.000 --> 17:13.083
COLLEEN: No.

17:13.083 --> 17:15.125
See, maybe you did
eat the pot roast.

17:15.125 --> 17:17.875
Okay, the last thing I remember
is taking a sleeping pill.

17:17.875 --> 17:20.166
Oh, yeah, that’s a thing.

17:20.166 --> 17:21.834
Sleeping pill haze.

17:21.834 --> 17:23.000
Maybe that’s it.

17:23.000 --> 17:24.750
My friend Brad,
he was taking them.

17:24.750 --> 17:27.375
He had no idea that he bought
a purple Miata online

17:27.375 --> 17:29.250
in the middle of the night,
and then the next night--

17:29.250 --> 17:31.458
you know that movie
<i>We Bought a Zoo--</i>

17:31.458 --> 17:32.875
he bought it on Blu-ray.

17:32.875 --> 17:35.333
-Oh, G--that’s it, okay.
-Mm-hmm.

17:35.333 --> 17:37.417
These sleeping pills
are costing me too much money.

17:37.417 --> 17:40.166
I can’t afford to sleep.

17:40.166 --> 17:42.583
♪

17:45.000 --> 17:47.208
-Pst, Matt, I can’t sleep.
-Hmm?

17:47.208 --> 17:49.250
I keep thinking
about the wedding.

17:49.250 --> 17:50.959
No, baby, you look great.

17:50.959 --> 17:52.500
(sighs)

17:56.375 --> 17:59.125
Oh, you don’t have
to bury your condoms

17:59.125 --> 18:00.834
at the bottom of the trash.

18:00.834 --> 18:02.792
I know you guys do it.

18:02.792 --> 18:04.417
I’m looking for
my sleeping pills.

18:04.417 --> 18:05.375
I need them.

18:05.375 --> 18:07.000
Mm, I know what that’s like,

18:07.000 --> 18:08.750
craving something
you can’t have,

18:08.750 --> 18:11.750
like a bra that fits
your beans just right.

18:11.750 --> 18:13.375
What are you still doing up?

18:13.375 --> 18:14.709
You can’t sleep either?

18:14.709 --> 18:17.709
Nah, I have to be up early
for the Korean Snapchats.

18:17.709 --> 18:19.500
Ah, there they are.

18:19.500 --> 18:20.792
Whew.

18:20.792 --> 18:22.083
Well, if you’re gonna
be up anyway,

18:22.083 --> 18:23.291
would you mind
keeping an eye on me

18:23.291 --> 18:25.583
so I don’t do anything
crazy in my sleep?

18:25.583 --> 18:27.250
I’ve been doing that anyway.

18:27.250 --> 18:29.583
But it feels nice
to be asked.

18:29.583 --> 18:30.959
♪

18:34.083 --> 18:35.125
♪

18:35.125 --> 18:39.375
COLLEEN:
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no!

18:39.375 --> 18:42.208
Dougie, I thought you were
gonna watch me last night.

18:42.208 --> 18:43.917
Matt is going to kill me!

18:43.917 --> 18:45.208
No, this?

18:45.208 --> 18:47.375
This was
my post-church breakfast.

18:47.375 --> 18:49.750
You slept like a little baby
all night in my arms.

18:49.750 --> 18:51.500
-Oh, thank--
-I actually fed you

18:51.500 --> 18:53.041
-so you’d keep sleeping.
-Aw.

18:53.041 --> 18:54.834
DOUGIE: Well, by "fed you,"

18:54.834 --> 18:56.583
I mean my gum
fell in your mouth.

18:56.583 --> 18:58.375
MATT: Colleen?

18:58.375 --> 19:00.250
It wasn’t me,
this was all Dougie.

19:00.250 --> 19:02.917
Ah, did Dougie also invite
all of your contacts

19:02.917 --> 19:04.542
to follow your
Period Tracker app?

19:04.542 --> 19:05.458
What?

19:05.458 --> 19:07.834
Dougie, I thought you said
that I slept like a baby!

19:07.834 --> 19:11.709
I meant a baby who e-mails
about her period.

19:11.709 --> 19:14.417
All right, fine,
I took more sleeping pills.

19:14.417 --> 19:16.917
’Cause the stress of the wedding
is keeping me up at night,

19:16.917 --> 19:18.208
and I don’t know what to do.

19:18.208 --> 19:20.166
Oh, no,
okay, hey, hey, hey, hey.

19:20.166 --> 19:22.417
It has been so unfair
for me to burden you

19:22.417 --> 19:23.917
with planning this
whole wedding by yourself.

19:23.917 --> 19:25.500
It’s our wedding, right?

19:25.500 --> 19:26.417
I want to help!

19:26.417 --> 19:27.792
Just tell me what I can do.

19:27.792 --> 19:29.750
-Okay.
-Okay?

19:29.750 --> 19:31.208
(grunts, sniffles)

19:31.208 --> 19:32.250
-There you go.
-Whoa!

19:32.250 --> 19:33.583
Look at that.

19:33.583 --> 19:35.000
All that for
one little wedding.

19:35.000 --> 19:37.959
No, that’s just the flowers,
"A" through "F."

19:37.959 --> 19:39.041
Hmm?

19:39.041 --> 19:40.333
These are "G" through "K."

19:40.333 --> 19:42.959
(crunching)

19:42.959 --> 19:44.667
Get busy.

19:44.667 --> 19:51.625
♪

19:54.166 --> 19:55.792
Um, Colleen?

19:55.792 --> 19:57.083
I can’t sleep.

19:57.083 --> 19:58.792
Planning a wedding
is both the most boring

19:58.792 --> 19:59.959
and stressful thing
I’ve ever done.

19:59.959 --> 20:02.792
It’s like jury duty
that I’m paying for.

20:02.792 --> 20:04.041
Colleen?

20:04.041 --> 20:05.709
Uh...

20:05.709 --> 20:12.625
♪

20:23.458 --> 20:25.959
(gate creaking)

20:25.959 --> 20:28.375
♪

20:28.375 --> 20:30.291
Damn it, Matt.

20:30.291 --> 20:32.000
I knew it was only
a matter of time

20:32.000 --> 20:35.583
before I saw you like this.

20:35.583 --> 20:36.959
(groaning)

20:36.959 --> 20:43.875
♪

20:44.542 --> 20:51.458
♪
